title: Tři oříšky pro Popelku
description: Cinderella receives three magical nuts that help her win the prince's heart at the royal ball.

title: Peřinbaba
description: A feather fairy aids a young girl in her quest for happiness and love in this enchanting tale.

title: Obchod na korze
description: A Slovak carpenter becomes the overseer of a Jewish widow's shop during World War II, exploring moral dilemmas.

title: Jáchyme, hoď ho do stroje!
description: A young man gets caught in absurd situations with a malfunctioning film projector and a mysterious crew.

title: Páni kluci
description: A nostalgic look at the mischievous adventures of boys in a small town after World War II.

title: Vlny
description: Friends navigate personal struggles and complex relationships, exploring themes of love and loss.

title: Za sklom
description: The intertwined lives of high-rise residents reveal hidden secrets and personal challenges.

title: Mesto tieňov
description: A detective investigates mysterious disappearances in a crime-ridden city.

title: Pat a Mat
description: Two clumsy handymen hilariously bungle their DIY projects.

title: Arabela
description: A magical princess from a fairy tale world explores the real world, leading to adventurous mischief.

title: Mamaia
description: The movie tells the story of Matilda, an old woman that has to fight against a real-estate mogul in order to save her house. Tanase is a ruthless businessman who built his fortune on scamming people and evicting them from their homes. When he wants to kick Matilda out of her house, his luck comes to an end as the seemingly nice old lady manages to defend her property.

title: Liceenii (The Graduates)
description: The love story of two tenth-graders in Romania before the revolution.

title: Miami Bici
description: Miami Bici is the story of Ion and Ilie, two young people from a small dark city in Romania who go to Miami in the middle of winter, to live both the "American Dream" and the Romanian dream of "getting rich quick".

title: Nea Marin miliardar
description: A Romanian peasant, visiting a friend who is working at a hotel on the Black Sea Riviera, is mistaken for a look-alike rich American businessman.

title: Coborâm la prima
description: Several passengers remain locked in a subway station. They do not know each other and each has a different route, with own problems. But as passengers interact, things change and everyone will have the same destination at the end

title: La Bloc
description: The lives and misadventures of a group of families living in a block from Bucharest.

title: Vlad
description: After being sent behind bars by the ones closest to him, a young man changes his identity and seeks revenge.

title: Profu'
description: It is a dramatic comedy, which focuses on Mihai Iacob, a character played by Andi Vasluianu, who returns to the chair after a period of absence, but who manages to bring young people to study.

title: Las Fierbinti
description: A Romanian sitcom with drama in a small village in Muntenia, Fierbinti, renamed Las Fierbinti.

title: Inimă de țigan (Gypsy Heart)
description: Gypsy Heart is a story about love and passion, dreams and restrictions, ambition and failure. Codrut, a young Gypsy man with ambitions to become a doctor and integrate the Romanian community, must obey the traditions of his ethnic group. But he falls in love with Irina (Andreea Patrascu), a very rich and spoiled Romanian girl whose father wants her to marry Luca, a successful businessman. Since Codrut's father promised him to a Gypsy girl and Irina is supposed to marry Luca, their love seems impossible, so they must fight everyone so they can be together. Gypsy Heart sheds light on the bohemian, traditional, romantic side of the Gypsy minority.

title: Verdes Anos
description: A story of a young couple moving to Lisbon in search of a new life.

title: Venus Velvet
description: A contemplative short film reflecting on themes of love and separation.

title: O Movimento das Coisas
description: A portrayal of daily life in a rural Portuguese village.

title: Vale Abraão
description: A take on 'Madame Bovary' set in rural Portugal.

title: A Comédia de Deus
description: A darkly humorous and provocative film exploring themes of religion and sensuality.

title: Os Mutantes
description: Story of troubled teenagers navigating harsh social realities.

title: A Metamorfose dos Pássaros
description: A poetic documentary exploring family and memories.

title: Alice
description: A father obsessively searches Lisbon for his missing daughter.

title: Tabu
description: A mysterious and poetic look at colonial Africa and Portugal.

title: Capitães de Abril
description: Chronicles Portugal's Carnation Revolution.

title: A Limousine the Colour of Midsummer's Eve
description: The struggle of two related families for the eighty-year-old aunt's inheritance through comic and romantic events.

title: Blow, the Winds (Pūt, vējiņi)
description: Uldis plans to marry the rich daughter of a landowner, but meets an orphan servant girl Baiba on his fiancé's property and falls madly in love.  The restrained Baiba reciprocates the feelings, but is conflited as whatever decision she makes someone would get hurt.

title: Four White Shirts
description: In his free time phone technician Cezars Kalnins composes songs about prevalent social issues for the band he founded with his friends. However he has a long way to go to circumvent the Soviet censorship and perform the songs publically.

title: A Short Instruction in Love Affairs
description: A young farmers boy experience in a quest for a bride.

title: Littlefinger
description: Littlefinger (Spriditis) is having a hard time living with the evil stepmother and despite his grandmother's and Lienite's attempts to dissuade him, he goes out into the world to find happiness.

title: The Devil's Servants
description: Three young men fight to prevent surrender of the city of Riga city to Swedish and Polish enemies.

title: The Devil's Servants at the Devil's Mill
description: Three brave young men interfere with the Swedish forces during a battle over Riga and the city remains in the hands of Riga citizens. Part 2 of "The Devil's Servants".

title: Lake Sonata
description: Doctor Rudolfs spends the summer in the countryside where he meets teacher Laura, the mother of two children whose husband is in prison. Rudolfs falls in love with Laura but she struggles with sense of duty to her family.

title: Emil's Mischiefs
description: The Svensson family lives in a farm called Katthult in Sweden. The younger son Emil's kindness and energy make him interfere with everything around him but the results are usually not what he initially intended.

title: A Gift to a Lonely Woman
description: In order to catch some thieves a beautiful detective comes up with a plan. An old lady wins a car and the thieves get excited.

title: The Price of Madness
description: Stories of relationships taking place in the fictional Petersons' hotel. The plot revolvs around members of the guests, hotel owners and employees

title: The Palace  Boarding house
description: Based on a novel by Anslavs Eglitis, a poet and his two sons are trying to use a gifted, run-down castle by setting up a boarding house in it. The castle comes with its set of old servants. Various misunderstandings with guests, servants, romantic adventures, visits of artists from the capital follow.

title: The Sweet Taste of Poisen
description: Based on a novel by Janis Jaunsudrabins "The New Landlord and the Devil". The Krastu couple moves to the countryside where the housband starts an affair with an infamous local woman.

title: Inspectors Grauds
description: TV Series about the loyal relationship between detective Ilmars and his faithful dog.

title: The Games of Shadows
description: Detective series revolving around private investigators and partners Roberts Meirans un Gabriela Ozoliņa.

title: Women lie better
description: TV Series follow four young women and their love interests.

title: Ida
description: Directed by Paweł Pawlikowski, this Oscar-winning film follows a young nun named Anna, who is about to take her vows. Before doing so, she learns about her Jewish heritage and embarks on a journey with her estranged aunt to discover the truth about her family's past during World War II.

title: The Pianist
description: Roman Polanski's autobiographical film tells the story of Władysław Szpilman, a Jewish pianist who struggles to survive the horrors of World War II in Warsaw. As he faces unimaginable adversity, the film beautifully portrays the resilience of the human spirit.

title: Człowiek z marmuru (Man of Marble)
description: Directed by Andrzej Wajda, this film explores the life of a young filmmaker who investigates the life of a legendary socialist worker. It critiques the communist regime in Poland, highlighting the struggles between personal ambition and political ideology.

title: Wesele (The Wedding) (2004)
description: A darkly humorous take on a wedding celebration in a small Polish village. The film reveals the underlying tensions and secrets of the family and guests, exploring themes of tradition, love, and societal expectations.

title: Kler (Clergy)
description: This provocative drama follows three Catholic priests who grapple with their faith and the challenges of their profession. The film exposes the dark side of the church, including corruption and moral dilemmas, sparking significant discussion in Polish society.

title: Zimna wojna (Cold War)
description: A tale of love set against the backdrop of the Cold War, this film follows a passionate romance between a musician and a singer. Directed by Paweł Pawlikowski, it beautifully captures the impact of political turmoil on personal relationships.

title: Dług (Debt)
description: A gripping drama inspired by true events, it follows two friends who become entangled in the criminal underworld after accumulating significant debt. The film explores themes of loyalty, desperation, and moral compromise.

title: Psy (Dogs)
description: Directed by Władysław Pasikowski, this crime drama centers on a former police officer who becomes embroiled in the dark world of organized crime. With its gritty portrayal of post-communist Poland, the film is a cult classic.

title: Cicha noc (Silent Night)
description: This film depicts a family reunion during Christmas Eve, where tensions rise and secrets come to light. Directed by Piotr Domalewski, it offers a poignant exploration of family dynamics, tradition, and the struggles of modern life in Poland.

title: Córki Dancingu (The Lure)
description: A unique blend of horror and musical, this film tells the story of two mermaid sisters who become part of a cabaret in 1980s Warsaw. As they navigate love and the human world, the film explores themes of identity, desire, and sacrifice.
